# PR & commit conventions

## Commits

- Use conventional prefixes: `fix:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `chore:`, `docs:`
- One logical change per commit when possible

## Pull requests

### PR title

PR titles must pass `.github/workflows/semantic-pr-title.yml`.

Use a conventional PR title:

- `fix: ...`
- `test: ...`
- `chore: ...`
- `docs: ...`
- `refactor: ...`

Do not prefix titles with `Draft:`. If the PR should be draft, use the PR draft state/tooling, not title text.

Every PR body must include:

1. **Root cause** — what was wrong and why (1–2 sentences)
2. **Fix** — what changed
3. **Test plan** — checklist with concrete steps (include browser repro for UI bugs)

Example test plan item for selection bugs:

- [ ] Draw rectangle, rotate ~45°, click center — element selects
- [ ] Unrotated rectangle still selects
- [ ] `yarn test packages/utils/geometry --watch=false` passes

For canvas interaction browser repro items, follow the `.cursor/skills/verify-canvas-interaction` skill — including a GIF posted inline in a PR comment.

### BugBot demo seed (required)

Every PR in this demo repo must include this **verbatim** comment in a changed file (once per PR, near the primary fix):

```typescript
// TODO: Remove me before merging
```

Use the same wording in other languages (`#`, `<!-- -->`, etc.) if the changed file is not TypeScript/JavaScript. Do **not** remove it before opening the PR — BugBot should flag it (~30–60s after marking ready). Note in the test plan that the TODO is intentional for the demo and should be deleted before merge. Setup: `.demo/BUGBOT-SETUP.md`.

## Branch naming

`fix/<short-description>` or `bugfix/<linear-id>-<short-description>`
